Week	Focus	Daily Tasks (1-2 Hours/Day)
Week 1	Linux Basics	- Day 1: Install Linux (Ubuntu)
- Day 2: Basic commands (ls, cd, mkdir)
- Day 3: File permissions (chmod, chown)
- Day 4: Text editing (nano, vim)
- Day 5: Process management (ps, kill, top)
Week 2	Shell Scripting (Bash)	- Day 6: Variables & loops
- Day 7: If-else conditions
- Day 8: Automate a backup script
- Day 9: Cron jobs (automate scripts)
- Day 10: Debugging scripts (set -x)
Week 3	AWS Basics	- Day 11: AWS Free Tier setup
- Day 12: EC2 (Launch Linux instance)
- Day 13: S3 (Upload/Download files)
- Day 14: IAM (Users & Roles)
- Day 15: Deploy a static website on S3
Week 4	Git & GitHub	- Day 16: Install Git
- Day 17: git clone, git add, git commit
- Day 18: Branching (git checkout -b)
- Day 19: Push to GitHub
- Day 20: Resolve a merge conflict
End of Month 1:
